cs.SE, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.CE 

The paper discusses empirical software engineering and productivity in open source software production, which suggests that cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category. The paper also touches on social and collective intelligence, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses measurement and methodology, which could be relevant to cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.SD (Software Development and Programming Languages). Finally, the paper discusses management and team performance, which could be relevant to cs.CE (Computers and Society).
